<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 1056/97 of 11 June 1997 adapting to technical progress Council Regulation (EEC) No 3821/85 on recording equipment in road transport </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1056/97, millega kohandatakse tehnika arenguga n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 3821/85 autovedudel kasutatavate s&otilde;idumeerikute kohta 11. juuni 1997 </eesti>
<inglise> (Text with EEA relevance) </inglise>
<eesti> (EMPs kohaldatav tekst) </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 3821/85 of 20 December 1985 on recording equipment in road transport (1), as last amended by Commission Regulation (EC) No 2479/95 (2), and in particular Article 17 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 20. detsembri 1985. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 3821/85 maanteevedudel kasutatavate s&otilde;idumeerikute kohta, (1) viimati muudetud komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2479/95, eriti selle artiklit 17, ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary to eliminate any possibility of fraud in the use of electronic recording equipment in road transport; </inglise>
<eesti> on vaja k&otilde;rvaldada mis tahes pettusev&otilde;imalused maanteevedudel kasutatavate elektrooniliste s&otilde;idumeerikute kasutamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Regulation (EC) No 2479/95 makes it compulsory to protect the cables connecting the recording equipment to the transmitter unless equivalent protection against manipulation is guaranteed by other means (for example by electronic monitoring such as signal encryption); whereas a joint consisting of sealed connections is deemed to be continuous; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2479/95 muudetakse kohustuslikuks s&otilde;idumeerikut saatjaga &uuml;hendavate kaablite kaitsmine, kui ei tagata samav&auml;&auml;rne manipuleerimisvastane kaitse muude vahenditega (n&auml;iteks elektrooniline seire signaali kr&uuml;pteerimise abil); kinnistest l&uuml;litustest koosnevat &uuml;hendust loetakse katkematuks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the recording equipment installed in all new vehicles put into service for the first time after 1 January 1996 has to be in conformity with the present Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> esmakordselt p&auml;rast 1. jaanuari 1996 kasutusele v&otilde;etavatesse k&otilde;ikidesse uutesse s&otilde;idukitesse paigaldatud s&otilde;idumeerikud peavad vastama k&auml;esolevale m&auml;&auml;rusele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas industry and motor-vehicle manufacturers experienced serious problems with the installation of armoured cables in category M 1 and N 1 vehicles, where the speed/distance impulses are generated by integrated sensors or ABS sensors; </inglise>
<eesti> t&ouml;&ouml;stusharul ja mootors&otilde;idukite tootjail oli t&otilde;siseid probleeme soomustatud kaablite paigaldamisega M 1 ja N 1 kategooriasse kuuluvatele s&otilde;idukitele, kus kiiruse/vahemaa impulsse tekitavad integreeritud andurid v&otilde;i ABS-andurid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas these sensors are not designed for the installation of an armoured cable; whereas it is necessary to permit that the armoured cable should not be compulsory for the connection between the sensor and the adaptor but only from the adaptor to the recording equipment; whereas it is consequently necessary to amend the Regulation accordingly; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealused andurid ei ole m&otilde;eldud soomustatud kaabliga &uuml;hendamiseks; on vaja s&auml;testada, et soomustatud kaabel ei ole kohustulik anduri ja adapteri &uuml;hendamisel, vaid see on kohustulik ainult adapteri ja s&otilde;idumeeriku vahel; j&auml;relikult tuleb m&auml;&auml;rust vastavalt muuta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Committee for the adaptation of Regulation (EEC) No 3821/85 to technical progress, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3821/85 kohandamist tehnika arenguga k&auml;sitleva komitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The following paragraphs should be added to point 5 of Chapter V, of Annex I to Regulation (EEC) No 3821/85. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3821/85 I lisa V peat&uuml;ki punkti 5 tuleks lisada j&auml;rgmised l&otilde;iked: </eesti>
<inglise> 'For the purpose of the application of the present point, M 1 and N 1 vehicles are those defined in Part A of Annex II to Council Directive 70/156/EEC (*). </inglise>
<eesti> "K&auml;esoleva punkti kohaldamisel kasutatakse M 1 ja N 1 kategooriasse kuuluvate s&otilde;idukite puhul n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 70/156/EM&Uuml;* II lisa A osa m&auml;&auml;ratlusi. </eesti>
<inglise> For those vehicles that are equipped with tachographs in compliance with the Regulation and are not designed to install an armoured cable between the distance and speed sensors and the recording equipment, then an adaptor shall be fitted as close as possible to the distance and speed sensors. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rusekohaselt tahhograafiga varustatud s&otilde;idukitele, millele ei saa paigaldada soomustatud kaablit vahemaa- ja kiirusesensorite ning s&otilde;idumeeriku vahele, paigaldatakse adapter v&otilde;imalikult vahemaa- ja kiiruseandurite l&auml;hedale. </eesti>
<inglise> The armoured cable shall be fitted from the adaptor to the recording equipment. </inglise>
<eesti> Adapter ja s&otilde;idumeerik &uuml;hendatakse soomustatud kaabliga. </eesti>
<inglise> (*) OJ No L 42, 23.2.1970, p. 1. </inglise>
<eesti> * E&Uuml;T L 42, 23.02.1970, lk 1." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the 20th day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kahek&uuml;mnendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply as from 1 January 1996. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse alates 1. jaanuarist 1996. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 11 June 1997. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 11. juuni 1997 </eesti>
